ederlöf retells the history of the Cuban Revolution as one of profound environmental and infrastructural change. In doing so, he opens up new questions about energy transitions, their politics, and the conditions of a socially just low-carbon future. The Cuban experience shows how a society can transform itself while rapidly cutting carbon emissions in the search for sustainability.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCarbon dioxide mitigationxEconomic aspectszCuba. 0aCarbon dioxide mitigation-Economic aspects-Cuba. 0aEnergy conservationzCuba. 0aEnergy conservation-Cuba. 0aEnergy policyzCuba. 0aEnergy policy-Cuba. 0aEnergy transitionxPolitical aspectszCuba. 0aEnergy transition-Political aspects-Cuba. 0aGeopoliticszCuba. 0aGeopolitics-Cuba. 0aInfrastructure (Economics)zCuba. 0aInfrastructure (Economics)-Cuba. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131921608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023z9783111318615oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520393141?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520393141423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520393141/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131921-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-1